snippet.textDisplay: Tickets did not sell out within minutes/days/ or a week. They still have a couple hundred non resale tickets available at t mobile arena website. So it was basically a shit ton of people that had all the tickets locked up. For the 1st hour or so then it kind of leveled off. I had to spam refresh "Oh no, no seats are available" about 10 times to be able to get a shot at tickets somebody didn't end up buying after the 2 minute hold. Since everybody had them locked up (2 mins repeated over by thousands of people) you just had to spam refresh and it would give you a random ticket somebody released. You'd then  have to look at the map and see where it was and if you wanted it. If not just keep repeating the process. Spam refresh on find tickets, if not a good one release it back. snippet.textDisplay: I think Conor McGregor is going to easily beat Cerrone. I love Cerrone he is one of my favorite Fighters. I have been watching him since he was in the WEC. McGregor was never I was really not fond of him. He was a lot more humble when he was younger and still hungry ,before the UFC. Even then though I guess he would do interviews where he would act the same way he does now. So there are things I don't like about the guy ,but I respect him and he is a successful person and a good fighter. He likes those long punches from the outside and the counters with some unpredictable movments. Cerrone is more of a technical fighter who is good on the inside,some pretty good hands and really good kicks plus grappling,but I just don't think Cerrone is a fluid enough fighter when it comes to his movements and beating Conor McGregor.  Not unless Conor McGregor looks like shit or something happens like they get into a clinch or grapple. I think Connor is going to back off mostly ,he's going to back away and he is going to hit him with long far punches from the outside. He's going to counter a lot of cerrone's moves while backing away. If Cerrone pushes forward then he may get caught pretty easily. I do know one thing though McGregor could take more of a hit probably then Cerrone. I seen McGregor take some good hits against Chad Mendes and others like khabib. Cerrone even though he is great hall of fame fighter and fighting at his best he tends to get TKO pretty easily. Once he gets flurried with a bunch of hard punches it over with hard punchers. Conor McGregor is known for punching hard and look what he did to Eddie Alvarez. Eddie Alvarez is a person who's known for fighting like a mad dog and taking punches Cerrone is not. Eddie Alvarez was shocked and hell once he felt what Connor's punches felt like he was in trouble.
